%% Diagram: W3C Trace Context propagation across three services
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Client
    participant Gateway as Edge / Gateway
    participant Orders as Orders service
    participant Payments as Payments service
    participant Backend as Trace backend

    Client->>Gateway: HTTP POST /checkout
    Note over Gateway: Generate root span<br/>traceparent: 00-{trace}-{spanA}-01
    Gateway->>Orders: HTTP call + traceparent + tracestate
    Note over Orders: Extract context, start child span<br/>parent = spanA, new spanB
    Orders->>Payments: HTTP call + traceparent (spanB) + baggage
    Note over Payments: Child span spanC<br/>read baggage user.tier=premium
    Payments-->>Orders: 200 OK
    Orders-->>Gateway: 200 OK
    Gateway-->>Client: 200 OK

    par Async export
        Gateway->>Backend: Export spanA
    and
        Orders->>Backend: Export spanB
    and
        Payments->>Backend: Export spanC
    end
    Note over Backend: Reassemble DAG by trace-id<br/>(spans arrive out of order)
